README.txt
==========

NAME
----
slurpfiles - concatenate non-binary files in a directory and print the content


SYNOPSIS
--------
slurpfiles [OPTIONS] [TARGET_DIR]


DESCRIPTION
-----------
This utility concatenates non-binary files in the specified target directory
and prints the content. The filename and relative path are printed atop each
text blob. By default, the current directory is used as the target directory.


OPTIONS
-------
TARGET_DIR
    The target directory to process. Default: current directory.

-r, --recursive
    Process subdirectories recursively.

--ignore PATTERN [PATTERN...]
    Ignore files matching specified patterns (e.g., *.css).


EXAMPLES
--------
Concatenate files in /optional/path:
    slurpfiles /optional/path

Concatenate files in /path/with/nested/dirs recursively:
    slurpfiles -r /path/with/nested/dirs

Concatenate files in /path while ignoring *.css and *.txt files:
    slurpfiles --ignore *.css --ignore *.txt /path


